article.description: Sacramento St. edges past UC Davis 73-67
article.headline: Sacramento St. edges past UC Davis 73-67
article.linkText: Sacramento St. edges past UC Davis 73-67
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Mikh McKinney scored a game-high 25 points -- including 10-for-10 from the free-throw line -- as Sacramento State edged past UC Davis in a close game down the stretch on Tuesday night. The Hornets (2-2) scored 10 points from the line in the final 28 seconds, McKinney hitting six and Cody Demps and Zach Mills a pair apiece. Demps scored 11 points, Mills 10 and Jordan Salley 11. Dreon Bartlett hit back-to-back 3-pointers -- his only baskets of the game -- to push Sacramento State up 56-50 with 6:02 to play. Josh Ritchart led UC Davis (3-4) with 20 points and Corey Hawkins added 16 and Ryan Sypkens 10. The Aggies held nine- and 10-point leads through much of the first half until Sacramento State used an 11-2 run to catch up.
